<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. SUPREME COURT OVERTURNS 'OPINION DEFENSE' IN LIBEL CASES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
1984 is here, six years late. Conrad's cartoon makes the point that the libel 
ruling will stifle opinion, and thus I say, stifle dissent. 
</P>
<P>
Now our government has apparently decided on "thought control" beyond its 
attacks on free speech and a free press. 
</P>
<P>
Can't we see where this Republican-appointed Supreme Court is taking us? 
</P>
<P>
JIM MOORE 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 
</P>
