<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. SUPREME COURT OVERTURNS 'OPINION DEFENSE' IN LIBEL CASES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Now The Supreme Court has ruled that the media, and even individuals, can be 
sued for libel even when statements are made as opinion. 
</P>
<P>
This is my opinion: This wrinkled pack of rabid fascist dogs have gone far 
enough in trying to restrict our rights. Chief Justice William H. Rehnquist is 
a prime candidate for euthanasia, although, even when dead, worms would avoid 
his carcass like feminists avoid adult bookstores. 
</P>
<P>
If Rehnquist, or one of his ancient cronies, wants to sue me for libel, then so 
be it. As King Lear said, "Let it come down." 
</P>
<P>
ANTHONY R. MUNROE 
</P>
<P>
Claremont 
</P>
