<P>
KAISER WORKERS OK THREE-YEAR CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Employees at Kaiser Permanente represented by Office and Professional Employees 
International Union Local 30 voted overwhelmingly over the weekend to ratify a 
three-year contract that calls for wage increases ranging from 11% to 16% over 
the next three years. Local 30 members voted on the pact after management and 
union negotiators reached agreement. Just over 90% of the votes cast were in 
favor of the contract. 
