<P>
SEASTRAND WIDOW TO SEEK ASSEMBLY SEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andrea Seastrand, widow of Assemblyman Eric Seastrand of Salinas, announced she 
will run for her husband's seat. Eric Seastrand, 52, an assembly member since 
December, 1982, died June 20 of cancer. 
</P>
<P>
His district includes portions of Monterey, San Luis Obispo and Santa Barbara 
counties. "My children are in college now, and I have reached that point in my 
life where I can devote my undivided attention to serving in the tradition of 
my late husband," said Andrea Seastrand, 49. The GOP central committees in the 
three counties must meet to select a replacement for the November ballot by 
Aug. 30. Only one other Republican has expressed interest, Steve MacElvainy, a 
member of the state Coastal Commission. Since the district leans Republican by 
a 48% to 40% margin, the chosen candidate has a leg up in the race. 
</P>
