<P>
The Heart of Rock 'n' Roll: Grammy winner Bonnie Raitt, who performed at the 
freedom rally honoring Nelson Mandela in Oakland Saturday, said Mandela told 
her that he credits the Wembley rock concert tribute to him two years ago with 
focusing attention worldwide on the anti-apartheid struggle. She said Mandela 
was especially pleased by the number of young people who were politicized about 
the issue, thanks to the concert. Raitt, who talked with Mandela at the African 
National Congress fund-raiser Friday night, said that's why Mandela made a 
special point of thanking musicians at this year's Wembley concert. GREG 
BRAXTON 
