MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Art Conference: For the first time in its 25-year history, the International 
Committee for Modern Art Museums will hold its annual meeting in Los Angeles. 
The conference, Sept. 8-15, is expected to draw a distinguished group of 
directors and chief curators of modern and contemporary art museums throughout 
the world. Members represent 33 countries including the Soviet Union, 
Czechoslovakia, Spain, Japan, Israel and Australia. GREG BRAXTON 
