<P>
STEALTH ATTACK: Heeding fears of increased airport noise, Congress last year 
passed a law to assure that commercial carriers couldn't use the El Toro Marine 
Corps Air Station. . . . But that hasn't stopped Federal Express from a second 
quiet attempt to use the base for its cargo jets. At the behest of Sen. Wendell 
H. Ford (D-Ky.), congressional investigators will visit El Toro July 11 to look 
once again into the idea of "joint civil/military use" of the base. . . . Rep. 
