</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dionex Corp., a San Jose maker of analytical instruments, will sell and 
distribute directly in Japan, one of the last countries where it sells through 
distributors. 
</P>
<P>
The change will result in a pretax charge of about $900,000 in the fourth 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
The company has agreed to buy certain assets from its former Japanese 
distributor, including $250,000 worth of Dionex inventory, for $1.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
After the change, about 90% of Dionex sales worldwide will be through its own 
direct sales force. 
</P>
