<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
WIFE QUOTED AS WARNING BARRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Washington Mayor Marion Barry's wife says she warned him another woman would be 
his downfall. 
</P>
<P>
"I told him all along: 'You're going to be set up with a woman,' " Effi Barry 
was quoted as saying in today's New York Post. 
</P>
<P>
"My gut (feeling) was that this would be his downfall." 
</P>
<P>
The FBI used former model Rasheeda Moore on Jan. 18 to lure Barry to a 
Washington hotel, where he was videotaped smoking crack. 
</P>
<P>
She said "one never knows" if her marriage will last, and she blamed alcoholism 
for her husband's troubles. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Barry said she had no knowledge of any cocaine use by her husband. 
</P>
<P>
"The times I've seen him incapacitated were due to drink," she said. "Those 
other alleged activities were when I wasn't present, so at this trial I, too, 
may learn things." 
