<P>
ATTORNEY-ACTOR'S CAREERS COLLIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NASHVILLE, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Attorney Fred Thompson was in court and had to miss the opening of "Days of 
Thunder" to see his performance as an auto racing magnate. 
</P>
<P>
Thompson also may be too busy this week to see the premiere of "Die Hard 2: Die 
Harder," in which he plays an embattled air traffic controller. 
</P>
<P>
Thompson, who makes a hobby of playing no-nonsense characters, was trying to 
settle a civil matter in Dallas and New Orleans when "Days of Thunder," 
starring Tom Cruise, opened. 
</P>
<P>
The attorney's specialty is defending people accused of white-collar crimes. He 
has offices in Nashville and Washington. 
</P>
